    &lt;CommentText&gt;My husband visited A&amp;amp;amp;E after suffering a thumb injury during the early hours of Monday morning.  The staff re-bandaged his thumb, sent him for x-ray and then left him to wait for 
 2 hours.  He was then told to attend the QE for 08.00 and they would advise that we were coming in and send over the x-rays.  When we did get to the QE the department did not open until 10.00 and the x-rays were never sent.  The staff at Russells Hall  hospital did not clean the wound even though it had happened in a warehouse, he was offered no pain relief, did not receive a tetanus and was given no antibiotics.  All this was offered and carried out within the first hour whilst at the QE.  I have never had any other issues with the hospital before this but feel the care he was received was below standard especially as he was at risk off losing the tip of his thumb&lt;/CommentText&gt;
